{"type":"Film","id":"ES2022_052","slug":"es2022-052-el-comensal","title":{"native":"El comensal","english":"The Dinner Guest"},"release":{"type":"Theatrical release","date":"2022-05-26","year":2022},"filmType":"Fiction film","directors":[{"id":"Ángeles González Sinde","slug":"angeles-gonzalez-sinde","name":"Ángeles González Sinde","birthYear":1965,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Female identifying","nationality":"Spain"}],"genre":["Drama","Thriller"],"media":{"posterUrl":"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt13778976/mediaviewer/rm2497387777/?ref_=tt_ov_i","trailerUrl":"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt13778976/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0_tt_6_nm_1_in_0_q_El%2520comensal"},"synopsis":{"native":"Iciar y Fernando son jóvenes. Los dos atraviesan la experiencia más traumática de sus breves vidas: La pérdida de uno de los progenitores. Pero Fernando e Iciar no pueden compartir el dolor ni las estrategias para manejarlo. Viven en tiempos distintos. Fernando en 1977 en Bilbao se enfrenta al secuestro de su padre por parte de ETA. Iciar en 2011 en Navarra afronta el cáncer fulminante de su madre. A partir de esta inesperada pérdida, Iciar toma conciencia del trágico secuestro y asesinato de su abuelo, al que nunca conoció, a manos de ETA en 1977. Ante la negativa de Fernando, su padre, de hablar del asunto. Iciar se embarca por su cuenta en una reconstrucción de los tensos días del secuestro cuarenta años atrás. Gracias a su esfuerzo por sacar a la luz la memoria familiar, su padre y ella se reencontrarán en una nueva manera de mirar al pasado para vivir el futuro... Adaptación de la novela homónima autobiográfica de Gabriela Ybarra.","english":"Icíar and Fernando are young. They are both going through the most traumatic experience of their short lives: the loss of a parent. But Fernando and Icíar can neither share the pain nor the strategies for dealing with it. They live in different times. Fernando in 1977 in Bilbao faces the kidnapping of his father by ETA. Icíar in 2011 in Navarra faces her mother's fulminating cancer."},"production":[{"country":"Spain","share":"Majority coproducer"}],"characters":[{"id":"ES2022_052_01","film":"ES2022_052","person":{"id":"Ginés García Millán","slug":"gines-garcia-millan","name":"Ginés García Millán","birthYear":1964,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Male identifying","nationality":"Spain"},"age":"2: Late Middle Age (55-60)","gender":"Male identifying","sexuality":"Heterosexual","origin":"White Western European","class":"Upper Middle class","profession":"Employed","ability":"Able-bodied","assistedMobility":"No"},{"id":"ES2022_052_02","film":"ES2022_052","person":{"id":"Adriana Ozores","slug":"adriana-ozores","name":"Adriana Ozores","birthYear":1959,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Female identifying","nationality":"Spain"},"age":"3: Third Age (60-75)","gender":"Female identifying","sexuality":"Heterosexual","origin":"White Western European","class":"Upper Middle class","profession":"Unemployed","ability":"Chronic illness","assistedMobility":"Yes"},{"id":"ES2022_052_03","film":"ES2022_052","person":{"id":"Iñaki Miramón","slug":"inaki-miramon","name":"Iñaki Miramón","birthYear":1957,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Male identifying","nationality":"Spain"},"age":"3: Third Age (60-75)","gender":"Male identifying","sexuality":"Heterosexual","origin":"White Western European","class":"Upper Middle class","profession":"Employed","ability":"Able-bodied","assistedMobility":"No"},{"id":"ES2022_052_04","film":"ES2022_052","person":{"id":"Ane Gabarain","slug":"ane-gabarain","name":"Ane Gabarain","birthYear":1963,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Female identifying","nationality":"Spain"},"age":"2: Late Middle Age (55-60)","gender":"Female identifying","sexuality":"Unknown","origin":"White Western European","class":"Unknown","profession":"Unknown","ability":"Unknown","assistedMobility":"No"}],"roles":[{"person":{"id":"Adriana Ozores","slug":"adriana-ozores","name":"Adriana Ozores","birthYear":1959,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Female identifying","nationality":"Spain"},"role":"Suppo